<br>
ORIGINS OF MY POLICY<br>
Waaaaaaaayyyyyyy back when I lead my first raid I decided to follow Federation policy.  This policy states in part that<br>
*****<br>
It is considered to be good form for a portion of all money loot to be donated to the clerics to help cover the spell component costs incurred to help the group as a whole with buffs.<br>
*****<br>
I said &quot;Cool we will end up with mondo cleric buffs during the raid.  What can it cost me to hep the clerics pay for material components?&quot;  At this point in time my cleric had just hit lv 20 and didnt need any material components.  I had no idea what a peridot was or how much they cost.<br>
<br>
That first raid taught me very quickly.  Even with all the gemstone loot....After the counting was done i reimbursed clerics and chanters (they use peridots too) over 1200pp out of my own pocket.  All that and im sure that some of the clerics let me off light on what they had spent.  One of the clerics has used over 140 peridots and we had 3 clerics in the raid.<br>
<br>
With this painful learning experience under my belt i foumulated my loot rules.<br>
1) The Raid leader and Group leaders will be given the right to loot.<br>
2) Anything with a merchant selling value of over 10pp will go to the raid leader.<br>
3) Anyone who has used material components will meet at a designated place after the raid and will be reimbursed (either in cash or items) for the material components that they used in the raid<br>
4) There is a standing Raid Chest of at least 1Kpp in case of emergencies.  Emergencies include but are not limited to raid wipeouts where the bodies have to be summoned (coffins are 70 to 80pp i think), transportation problems to the raid site in case of wipeouts, and things of that nature.<br>
<br>
Any other loot uner 10pp of value i normaly drop on the ground.  Please feel free to pick it up if you want or need it.  Most of this stuff will be non stackable stuff like weapons or words and runes that have only a couple pp value each.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps to answer people's questions about what I do with the loot.<br>
<br>
Thank you <br>
